· Make continuous progress toward producing our products while causing no accidents, injuries or harm to the environment;
· Publicly report global health, safety and environmental performance;
· Lead our company in ethical ways that increasingly benefit society, the economy and the environment;
· Seek and incorporate public input regarding our products and operations;
· Provide chemicals that can be manufactured, transported, used and disposed of safely;
· Make health, safety, the environment and resource conservation critical considerations for all new and existing products and  processes;
· Provide information on health or environmental risks and pursue protective measures for employees, the public and other key stakeholders;
· Work with customers, carriers, suppliers, distributors and contractors to foster the safe use, transport and disposal of chemicals;
· Operate our facilities in a manner that protects the environment and the health and safety of our employees and the public;
· Support education and research on the health, safety and environmental effects of our products and processes;
· Work with others to resolve problems associated with past handling and disposal practices;
· Lead in the development of responsible laws, regulations and standards that safeguard the community, workplace and environment; and
· Encourage and assist others to adhere to these principals and practices.

